{
  "text": "Phagocytosis is a multistep process involving binding of particles to cell surface receptors, formation of endocytic vesicles termed phagosomes, maturation of phagosomes to phagolysosomes, and finally digestion within phagolysosomes through the action of acidic hydrolases [CITATION_1] .",
